text: Patricia Carricaburu (born 21 September 1988) is a French rugby union player. She was a member of the France women's national rugby union team. She played at the 2015 Women's Six Nations Championship, 2016 Women's Six Nations Championship, 2017 Women's Rugby World Cup, and 2018 Women's Six Nations Championship. She played for Lons Rugby Féminin Béarn Pyrénées. == References == Category:1988 births Category:Living people Category:French rugby union players Category:People from Pyrénées-Atlantiques Category:Sportspeople from Nouvelle-Aquitaine
